{
  "stem": "25591.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I couldn't buy anything.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I had no money at the train station.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I got some very sort of lukewarm water out of the tap, which was my drink.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I had some bread and salami that I brought with me from Hungary, and that was my food all the way through.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when-- when my ship arrived in New York, and this is the only moment when I could have turned profoundly anti-American, they took away had the remaining half of my salami because you're not supposed to bring food in the United States.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But I went to Cherbourg and got on the boat.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I remember a very large, black sailor was at the gangplank.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I told him my name, and I was on the list, and he said, your bunk is B20.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So I went to B20, put down my knapsack.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That's all I had.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they called for chow, and I didn't know what chow was, but I sort of figured it out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And at that stage of my life, this was August of '47 when food to me was still the most important thing in this world because I had been deprived of so much food.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And we had these huge metal trays on the line, and they gave me all I asked for, and I asked for more.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And my tray was just filled with everything-- potatoes and meat and vegetables and bread and milk and pie.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then at the end of the line-- I-- I-- I can see it as clearly as I can see you-- there was a huge wicker basket of oranges and a huge wicker basket of bananas.",
      "word_count": 36
    }
  ],
